React.js Chapter

a. What is the difference between state and props?
answer : 
Data from state can be modified by its own component
Data from props is read-only, and cannot be modified by a component

b. What are synthetic events in React? (Provide an example)
answer :
synthetic events is just like event handler in javascript
function sampleSyntheticEvents() {
  return (
    <button
      onClick={(e) => {
        console.log('This Button Clicked');
      }}
    />
  )
}

